sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant ClaudeCode as Claude Code<br/>(Session Context)
    participant SKILLMD as SKILL.md<br/>(Terse Launcher)
    participant gemini_run as scripts/gemini_run.py<br/>(Entry Point)
    participant Dispatch as dispatch.py<br/>(Command Router)
    participant Adapter as adapters/<br/>(Command-Specific)
    participant Facade as core/transport<br/>(3-Function Facade)
    participant Coordinator as TransportCoordinator<br/>(Backend Chooser)
    participant SDK as SdkTransport<br/>(SDK Backend)
    participant RawHTTP as RawHttpTransport<br/>(HTTP Backend)
    participant Normalize as normalize.py<br/>(Anti-Corruption)
    participant Gemini as Gemini API<br/>(Google)
    participant Stdout as stdout<br/>(Output)

    User->>ClaudeCode: Invokes gemini skill
    ClaudeCode->>SKILLMD: Reads SKILL.md
    Note over ClaudeCode,SKILLMD: Token budget:<br/>SKILL.md kept terse<br/>Reference files on-demand
    ClaudeCode->>gemini_run: Executes python3 gemini_run.py text "prompt"
    gemini_run->>Dispatch: parse args, route to command
    Dispatch->>Adapter: Call adapter for 'text' command
    Adapter->>Facade: api_call(request, timeout, retries)
    Facade->>Coordinator: Get coordinator (lazy singleton)
    Coordinator->>Coordinator: Check capability gate
    alt SDK Available & Priority
        Coordinator->>SDK: Try primary: api_call()
        SDK->>Gemini: POST /v1beta/models/gemini-2.5-flash:generateContent
        Gemini->>SDK: Response (REST envelope)
        SDK->>Normalize: normalize_response()
        Normalize->>SDK: Canonical dict shape
        SDK->>Coordinator: Return normalized response
    else SDK Unavailable or Fails
        Coordinator->>RawHTTP: Try fallback: api_call()
        RawHTTP->>Gemini: POST /v1beta/models/gemini-2.5-flash:generateContent
        Gemini->>RawHTTP: Response (REST envelope)
        RawHTTP->>Coordinator: Return response (already REST shape)
    end
    Coordinator->>Facade: Return response
    Facade->>Adapter: Return response
    Adapter->>Adapter: Format response (markdown, JSON, etc.)
    Adapter->>Stdout: Print result
    Stdout->>User: Display output
